# Apple Spinach Salad

> Bright and light. Can be a main dish if you add chicken, or act as a side. #salad #side #vegetarian

- Walnuts | 1/3 cup | Toasted and chopped

Toast walnuts in a dry pan until fragrant.

- Olive Oil | 2 tbsp | 
- Honey | Just a kiss | 
- Cider Vinegar | 1 tbsp | 
- Dijon Mustard | 1 tsp | 
- Black Pepper | to taste | 
- Salt | to taste | 

In a small bowl whisk together the oil, vinegar, honey, and mustard. Season with salt and pepper to taste

- Spinach | 5 cups | 

Toss the spinach with the dressing until evenly coated then divide the spinach among 4 serving plates

- Apple | Granny Smith, 1 | 

Core the apple and slice it into matchsticks. Sprinkle a quarter of the apple pieces on top of each salad. Follow with the walnut pieces. Serve immediately
